summary:
Growing up in diverse communities in various countries in the Global North and South has equipped me with strong multicultural competence, intercultural understanding, strong  communication skills in multiple languages, and an open-minded, inclusive, and tolerant perspective. Studying psychology, international development studies and cultural and social anthropology has equipped me with the necessary knowledge, tools, and lenses through which to approach important social, cultural, psychological, economic, and political issues

Special interests: Gender (in)equality, anti-discrimination, neo-colonialism, human-rights, inclusion & diversity 

Besides my interest in the public and semi-public sector, I have recently begun translating work, specifically Dutch to English (Freelance). I have been working for roughly one year with an NGO to translate their organisational work and currently working with an author to translate their published novel to expand its reach outside of the Netherlands.
